subSubSection.paragraph:
Bixa atlantica

is most similar to 

Bixa excelsa

, but differs in its insertion of the lowest primary vein in relation to midrib length (1/4 vs 1/ 
3 in

B. excelsa

), number of primary veins ((4–)5 vs. 3(–4) in 

B. excelsa

), corolla color (white vs. pinkish in 

B. excelsa

), fruit color when mature (reddish vs. greenish or brownish in 

B. excelsa

) and spine density in fruits (not obscuring the surface vs. obscuring the surface in 

B. excelsa

).
